Various emergency personnel have been mobilised in KZN as heavy rains continue to wreak havoc. For more, #eNCA speaks to eThekwini Municipality Deputy City Manager Musa Gumede. #DStv403 #KZNFloods JOHANNESBURG - The eThekwini Municipality has confirmed that one person has drowned following heavy rains in KwaZulu-Natal. More than 200 people have been evacuated in Umlazi, Durban North, and Verulam. READ: KZN Floods | Hundreds evacuated amid heavy rains "Since last night we have evacuated over 200 people, much less than the numbers that we saw a month ago when we evacuated over 10 000 people within two days, " said eThekwini Municipality Deputy City Manager Musa Gumede. Last month, deadly floods claimed over 400 lives.